Shugetsu 麵鮮醬油房 周月 - 銅鑼灣

reviews.text:
The best Tsukemen I have had in Hong Kong yet.

The noodles are made directly in the shop. You can choose either hot or more traditional cold noodles. The broth has a really rich and unique taste.
The place itself was immaculate, well air-conditioned and traditional Japanese looking. The waiter was super kind and courteous.

Highly recommend!
The soup is tasty, service is good.  But the noodles are stick to each other which makes me difficult to put them in the soup

Had diarrhoea after dinner there, it has to be that place cause I only ate one meal that day. On top of that it's winter, how do you even spoil food in winter unless you are in horrendous condition? Awful.

My favourite goes to texture of the cold noodles and them amazing soft boiled eggs. 

Everything else is average. Including the broth you use to dip the noodles in. 

A nice chill place for weekdays dinner dates tho.
Food was great, staff were very attentive and kind, design of restaurant was thoughtful
